326
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,600
It's called "Philosophers Speak".

327
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:48,270
Let me tell you.

328
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,910
In this show of his,

329
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:51,360
when he explains things

330
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,200
it's so profound yet simple.

331
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,080
It's so fascinating!

332
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,790
Wang Shiyan, my daughter,
has become a fan.

333
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:58,480
I watch every episode of
"Philosophers Speak"!

334
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,030
I'm so honored to meet you.

335
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:00,510
You flatter me.

336
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,390
In my firm's annual meeting,

337
00:12:02,390 --> 00:12:03,200
my boss asked me

338
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,600
to find a way

339
00:12:04,630 --> 00:12:06,080
to invite Professor Ding
to record a slogan.

340
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:08,000
I checked with MCN agencies for quotes.

341
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:08,480
They said

342
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,440
Professor Ding doesn't take just any job.

343
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,000
Exactly.

344
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,150
But look, now I've met you.

345
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,320
I'm sure we'll work something out.

346
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,390
Okay.

347
00:12:14,390 --> 00:12:15,200
Hey.

348
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:15,750
Shall we group

349
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:16,480
